				   #### aptsources ####

aptsources is a script for those who don't want or need a GUI to quickly modify
source entries in files under 'sources.list.d/'.

Usage: ./aptsources.sh [-e -s -d -a -r] [repository filename]
       -lp [ppa:user/ppa-name  ubuntu-codename] -l -h;'

Only one option can be specified at a time.
Omit '.list' extension in filename/repository name.

-e,  --enable      enable repository, only 'deb' line'
-s,  --src         enable repository, 'deb-src' and 'deb' lines'
-d,  --disable     disable repository'
-a,  --add         add repository'
-r,  --remove      remove repository'
-lp, --add-lp      add launchpad repository and fetch key'
-l,  --list        list repositories and status'
-h,  --help        this message'

Basically, it comments and uncomments deb or deb and deb-src lines for the
specified repository/filename, but it also shows the status of the repository
(enabled or disabled), or adds new repositories, as well as removing them.

To install system-wide, first do 'chmod +x aptsources.sh', and then you can either copy the file to /usr/local/bin, or create a link pointing to the location of the script.
